User Browser
     |
     | Type URL: https://www.google.com
     v
+------------------------+
|  DNS Resolver          |
|  - Translates domain   |
|    www.google.com      |
|    → IP address        |
+------------------------+
     |
     | Connect to server IP (TCP/IP, Port 443)
     v
+------------------------+
|      Firewall          |
|  - Inspects traffic    |
|  - Blocks malicious    |
+------------------------+
     |
     | Encrypted HTTPS traffic (TLS/SSL)
     v
+------------------------+
|    Load Balancer       |
|  - Distributes request |
|    to web servers      |
+------------------------+
     |
     v
+------------------------+
|     Web Server         |
|  - Serves static files |
|  - Forwards dynamic    |
|    requests to App     |
+------------------------+
     |
     v
+------------------------+
| Application Server     |
| - Generates dynamic    |
|   web page             |
| - Queries Database     |
+------------------------+
     |
     v
+------------------------+
| Database Server        |
| - Stores persistent    |
|   data                 |
| - Returns requested    |
|   information          |


Diagram Notes

DNS Resolution: User’s browser asks for IP before connecting.

Server IP & Port: HTTPS uses TCP port 443.

Traffic Encryption: TLS/SSL secures data between browser and server.

Firewall: Protects servers from unauthorized access.

Load Balancer: Distributes traffic for high availability.

Web Server: Serves static content or passes dynamic requests.

Application Server: Generates dynamic content.

Database: Supplies the data required by the application server.
+------------------------+
     |
     v
Back to Browser → Rendered web page
